#  Project settings

##  Configure project features and permissions  <::before>

To configure features and permissions for a project: 

  1. <::marker>On the left sidebar, select **Search or go to** and find your project. 
  2. <::marker>Select **Settings > General ** . 
  3. <::marker>Expand **Visibility, project features, permissions** . 
  4. <::marker>To allow users to request access to the project, select the **Users can request access** checkbox. 
  5. <::marker>To turn features on or off in the project, use the feature toggles. 
  6. <::marker>Select **Save changes** . 



###  Feature dependencies  <::before>

When you turn off a feature, the following additional features are also unavailable: 

  * <::marker>

If you turn off the **Issues** feature, project users cannot use: 

    * <::marker> **Issue Boards**
    * <::marker> **Service Desk**
    * <::marker>Project users can still access **Milestones** from merge requests. 
  * <::marker>

If you turn off **Issues** and **Merge Requests** , project users cannot use: 

    * <::marker> **Labels**
    * <::marker> **Milestones**
  * <::marker>

If you turn off **Repository** , project users cannot access: 

    * <::marker> **Merge requests**
    * <::marker> **CI/CD**
    * <::marker> **Git Large File Storage**
    * <::marker> **Packages**
  * <::marker>

The metrics dashboard requires read access to project environments and deployments. Users with access to the metrics dashboard can also access environments and deployments. 




##  Toggle project features  <::before>

Available project features are visible and accessible to project members. You can turn off specific project features, so that they are not visible and accessible to project members, regardless of their role. 

To toggle the availability of individual features in a project: 

  1. <::marker>On the left sidebar, select **Search or go to** and find your project. 
  2. <::marker>Select **Settings > General ** . 
  3. <::marker>Expand **Visibility, project features, permissions** . 
  4. <::marker>To change the availability of a feature, turn the toggle on or off. 
  5. <::marker>Select **Save changes** . 



##  Turn off project analytics  <::before>

By default, project analytics are displayed under the **Analyze** item in the left sidebar. To turn this feature off and remove the **Analyze** item from the left sidebar: 

  1. <::marker>On the left sidebar, select **Search or go to** and find your project. 
  2. <::marker>Select **Settings > General ** . 
  3. <::marker>Expand **Visibility, project features, permissions** . 
  4. <::marker>Turn off the **Analytics** toggle. 
  5. <::marker>Select **Save changes** . 



##  Turn off CVE identifier request in issues  <::before>

  * Tier  : Free, Premium, Ultimate 
  * Offering  : GitLab.com 



History 

  * [ Introduced ](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/merge_requests/41203) in GitLab 13.4, only for public projects on GitLab.com. 



In some environments, users can submit a [ CVE identifier request ](/user/application_security/cve_id_request/) in an issue. 

To turn off the CVE identifier request option in issues in your project: 

  1. <::marker>On the left sidebar, select **Search or go to** and find your project. 
  2. <::marker>Select **Settings > General ** . 
  3. <::marker>Expand **Visibility, project features, permissions** . 
  4. <::marker>Under **Issues** , turn off the **CVE ID requests in the issue sidebar** toggle. 
  5. <::marker>Select **Save changes** . 



##  Turn off project email notifications  <::before>

Prerequisites: 

  * <::marker>You must have the Owner role for the project. 


  1. <::marker>On the left sidebar, select **Search or go to** and find your project. 
  2. <::marker>Select **Settings > General ** . 
  3. <::marker>Expand the **Visibility, project features, permissions** section. 
  4. <::marker>Clear the **Enable email notifications** checkbox. 



###  Turn off diff previews in project email notifications  <::before>

History 

  * [ Introduced ](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/24733) in GitLab 15.6 [ with a flag ](/administration/feature_flags/) named ` diff_preview_in_email ` . Disabled by default. 
  * [ Generally available ](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/382055) in GitLab 17.1. Feature flag ` diff_preview_in_email ` removed. 



When you review code in a merge request and comment on a line of code, GitLab includes a few lines of the diff in the email notification to participants. Some organizational policies treat email as a less secure system, or might not control their own infrastructure for email. This can present risks to IP or access control of source code. 

Prerequisites: 

  * <::marker>You must have the Owner role for the project. 



To turn off diff previews for a project: 

  1. <::marker>On the left sidebar, select **Search or go to** and find your project. 
  2. <::marker>Select **Settings > General ** . 
  3. <::marker>Expand the **Visibility, project features, permissions** section. 
  4. <::marker>Clear **Include diff previews** . 
  5. <::marker>Select **Save changes** . 



##  Configure merge request settings for a project  <::before>

Configure your project’s merge request settings: 

  * <::marker>Set up the [ merge request method ](/user/project/merge_requests/methods/) (merge commit, fast-forward merge).
